##"I feel like a corn in my hazmat suit. "

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Wang Haihong

(the first group of Shanghai Medical Team members to support Hubei Province and the nurse of Shanghai Fengxian District Central Hospital)

It was cloudy in Wuhan on February 16.

Yesterday's Wuhan, under a day of snow. Snow flying all over the sky, fluttering asperses, the sky is gray, smoke wreathing.

I took a picture of the snow scene outside the window. It snowed in Wuhan. I wonder if it snowed in Shanghai? Do not know distant relatives wear more clothes have not? Is the quilt cold at night when you sleep?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wang Haihong and colleagues. Image courtesy of Wang Haihong

The medical team's wechat group posted several messages about the sudden drop in temperature, reminding team members to pay attention to keeping warm. I am the shift from 0:00 to 4:00 in the morning, obediently put on the team issued in advance of the military coat, their own tightly wrapped up.

At 2300 hours, local volunteer drivers in Wuhan were waiting in the hall. The driver, big brother, came all the way, took us to the hospital, then hurried back home, and had to get up early for work tomorrow. There are always some people, in the quiet to pay and dedication, this society or good people more ah!

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The snowscape of the hospital

The temperature dropped below 0 C in the early morning, making it the coldest weather in Wuhan so far. I'm wearing long johns underneath, and I'm wearing scrubs. Take off the military coat, first put on the nurse clothes, then put on the isolation clothes, finally put on the protective clothing, inside and outside a total of five layers, instantly feel like a corn.

The head and the face are even worse. N95 Masks, hats, isolation cloaks, goggles, protective clothing hats, face shields, each layer tightly strapped to the head, feeling like a journey to the West in the bound spell of Son Gok, with a skill to drive away evil spirits.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Street signs with snow

Fortunately, in our class, everything is stable, the patients are safe to sleep, we quietly guarding!

(by Chen Shaoying, reporter trainee, thepaper.cn)

This issue is edited by Chang Chen
